      • type

        public String type

        pretty self-explanatory, needed because this is a Subscribable object

      • timestamp

        public Long timestamp
        The time of last activity on this AccountActivity.

      • source

        public String source
        Where this AccountActivity came from.

        With accounts possible across different brokers, there may be some conflicting broker account IDs. The Bank must know where this account data came from so it can match it to the correct local account ID.

        Possible values: 

         Sim
 TDA

      • subscriptionkey

        public String subscriptionkey
        The subscription key.

      • accountnumber

        public String accountnumber
        The account # this AccountActivity is about.

      • messagetype

        public String messagetype
        The type of message.

        Possible values: 

         SUBSCRIBED - initially returned after subscribing to ACCT_ACTIVITY, no XML data returned
 ERROR - indicates an error, instead of XML values, it will be:
   INVALID_KEY - if the Message Key used in the subscription is invalid
   EXPIRED_KEY - if the key is more than 24 hours old at time of subscription
   SYSTEM_ERROR - some internal server error
 BrokenTrade - After an order was filled, the trade is reversed or "Broken" and the order is changed to Canceled
 ManualExecution - the order is manually entered by the broker.
 OrderActivation - a Stop order has been Activated
 OrderCancelReplaceRequest - a request to modify an order has been received
 OrderCancelRequest - a request to cancel an order has been received
 OrderEntryRequest - a new order has been submitted
 OrderFill - an order has been completely filled
 OrderPartialFill - an order has been partial filled
 OrderRejection - an order was rejected
 TooLateToCancel - a request to cancel an order has been received, but cannot be canceled
 UROUT - "You Are Out", the order has been canceled
